LINKING AID TO POPULATION GROWTH 




Rep. Anthony Beilenson's (D-Los Angeles) article on foreign aid and population 
growth (Commentary, July 23) was excellent. Mankind's slow response to the 
ever-more-serious growth of our population is leading us to disaster. 


The U.S. government must do more to assist anyone in the world who wants access 
to family planning. The dehumanizing poverty and declining standard of living 
for hundreds of millions of people in less-developed countries are reasons 
enough to do so. 


But help must be given for our own sake as well. The Dominican and Mexican 
population explosions illustrate why. The United States has been flooded with 
millions of poor, uneducated Dominicans and Mexicans, who have fled their 
countries and who now contribute to the overcrowding of our cities, 
particularly New York and Los Angeles. 


